Class ResultSetsFromPreparedStatementTest

  • java.lang.Object
    • junit.framework.Assert

    junit.framework.Test

    public class ResultSetsFromPreparedStatementTest
extends BaseJDBCTestCase
    Tests repeated instantiation of internal ResultSet types from PreparedStatements. This test will be a good sanity check when experimenting with re-use of internal ResultSet objects.

      • dump

        private static void dump(java.sql.ResultSet dumpee,
                         java.io.PrintStream stream)
                  throws java.sql.SQLException
        Prints a ResultSet to a PrintStream. The first line is a heading with name and type of each column. Each row is printed as a comma-separated list of columns. The printed value of a column is getObject(i).toString(). Closes the RS when done. Intended for debugging purposes.
        Parameters:
        dumpee - the ResultSet to dump
        stream - the stream to dump the ResultSet to
        Throws:
        java.sql.SQLException

      • dumpDiff

        private static void dumpDiff(java.lang.Object[][] expected,
                             int fromRow,
                             java.sql.ResultSet dumpee,
                             boolean moreRows,
                             java.io.PrintStream stream)
                      throws java.sql.SQLException
        Prints a diff between a ResultSet and an expected Object[][] value to a PrintStream. The first line is a heading with name and type of each column. Each row is printed as a comma-separated list of columns. The printed value of a column is getObject(i).toString().

        If the expected value does not match the value from the RS, the expected value is printed followed by the actual value in angle brackets. The comparion starts from 'fromRow' (zero-based row index). Unmatched rows are printed with 'null' for the missing values.

        dumpee must be positioned on a valid row, or moreRows must be false. Closes the RS when done.

        Parameters:
        expected - the expected value of the RS
        fromRow - row to start comparison from
        dumpee - the ResultSet to dump
        moreRows - true if there are more rows in the RS
        stream - the stream to dump the ResultSet to
        Throws:
        java.sql.SQLException

      • dumpObjectArray

        private static void dumpObjectArray(java.sql.ResultSet dumpee,
                                    java.io.PrintStream stream)
                             throws java.sql.SQLException
        Prints a ResultSet to a PrintStream in the form of an Object[][] constant that can be used as "expected outcome" in assertions. Closes the ResultSet when done. Experimental and not tested for data types other than String and Integer.
        Parameters:
        dumpee - the ResultSet to dump
        stream - the stream to dump the ResultSet to
        Throws:
        java.sql.SQLException
